    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1881</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Two bad errata &amp; a blunder have been discovered in my worm book<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>p. 134, 3 lines from bottom, for 1·9 read ·19</p>
                    <p>p. 165 5 lines from top, for 83·87 read 8·387</p>
                    <p>p. 284 6 lines from bottom for (mean 1° 49′) read (mean 2° 45′)</p>
                    <p>The book is selling largely in England.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>In Haste | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi></note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus was preparing the German translation of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9017.xml">Carus trans. 1882</ref>). The corrections were made in the fourth thousand of the English edition. The correction on p. 284 was also given in an errata sheet inserted in the third thousand (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml">Freeman 1977</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">On the sale of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13460.xml">letter from R. F. Cooke, 5 November 1881</ref>.</note>
            
            
        </div>
    
